cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.AL 

This paper deals with the problem of rerouting flows in a network, which is a common problem in communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions software-defined networks, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The problem of finding feasible update schedules is related to scheduling algorithms, which is covered in cs.AL (Algorithms). The paper also mentions congestion-free routing, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the runtime of the algorithm, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
